1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new method for locally-biased graph-based learning, which involves finding good conductance cuts near a set of seed vertices. This is a problem that falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new method for graph-based learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with graph-based learning, which is a topic that falls under the domain of social and information networks. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new method for solving graph-based learning problems, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper demonstrates the power of the proposed method by solving problems on a 467 million edge graph based on an MRI scan, which is a topic that falls under the domain of computer vision and pattern recognition.
